column8: P1. Permit all uses of human genome editing and mitochondrial donation only if not for profit
column9: P2. Prohibit all forms of human genome editing for now, except for research purposes.
column10: P3.  Permit only non-heritable human genome editing in both research and in clinics.
column11: P4. Permit only non-heritable human genome editing for clinical treatments, and mitochondrial donation.
column12: P5.  Permit both heritable and non-heritable uses of genome editing for any purpose with minimal restrictions to ensure safety and compliance with ethical standards.
column13: P6. Permit non-heritable and heritable human genome editing (including mitochondrial donation), but only for clinical purposes, and if there is strong oversight, regular community input and (re)approval.
column14: P7. Prohibit all uses of human genome editing and mitochondrial donation.
column15: P8. Permit only non-heritable human genome editing in both research and in clinics and mitochondrial donation only if not for profit.
